@startuml plugin-loading-workflow

title LogViewer - Plugin Loading Lifecycle

participant "Application" as App
participant "PluginManager" as PM
participant "PluginLoader" as PL
participant "Plugin DLL/SO" as DLL
participant "IPlugin Instance" as Plugin

App -> PM: DiscoverPlugins(searchPath)
activate PM

PM -> PM: Scan directories\nfor .so/.dll/.zip

PM -> PL: LoadPlugin(path)
activate PL

PL -> PL: Validate file\n(signature check)
PL -> DLL: dlopen(path)
activate DLL
DLL --> PL: Handle
deactivate DLL

PL -> PL: Extract metadata\nfrom library

PL -> DLL: Call plugin_create()\nC-ABI function
activate DLL
DLL -> Plugin: Create IPlugin instance
Plugin --> DLL: Instance pointer
deactivate DLL

PL --> PM: PluginHandle\n+ Metadata
deactivate PL

PM -> Plugin: Initialize()
activate Plugin
Plugin -> Plugin: Setup resources\nConnect callbacks
Plugin --> PM: Result::Ok
deactivate Plugin

PM -> PM: Register in map\nNotify observers
PM --> App: OK

note over PM
    Plugins are managed
    in a registry map
end note

... Later: Cleanup ...

App -> PM: UnloadPlugin(id)
PM -> Plugin: Shutdown()
PM -> DLL: Close handle
DLL -> Plugin: Destroy instance

note over PL
    C-ABI interface allows
    plugins from any compiler
    that supports C calling convention
end note

@enduml
